@kylapratt blew my entire world up in the best way possible with her early 2000's hit UPN show 'One on One'. In her I saw myself and believed that the career and life I have now was 1000% attainable. Kyla is a true multihyphenate who I am so very proud of. She exemplifies Black Girl Magic & she inspires me daily! 
Sidenote: Y'all remember Kyla in the 2003 B2K video for 'What A Girl Wants'? Whewwwwwww she's BEEN goals for decades!

Where there is progress, there is hope! Sometimes progress is big leaps & at other times, baby steps but the outcome is always beautiful because it ignites change! In 2008, while a junior at Howard University, America elected its first black president, President Obama. Now, in my 11th year living in Los Angeles, making my dreams come true, our first female and POC VP was elected. Nothing is more representative of progress than that. I feel so blessed to be a part of the beautiful and much deserved global recognition and wins in the black community & I commit to always contributing to progress in an uplifting and authentic way. @ashleyblaine

captions: Playing Erica Sinclair is an unbelievable experience. When I landed the role, I hadn‚Äôt seen many young Black girls represented in an international Sci-fi series. Erica was raised in an era where it wasn‚Äôt common for Black girls to use their voice. Especially in a fictional American town like Hawkins. Girls who looked like her were probably ignored and dismissed. I believe The Sinclairs encouraged & empowered their daughter, because she didn‚Äôt ‚Äúfit in‚Äù easily. She tapped into her purpose, maybe earlier than most, a bit ahead of her time. I‚Äôm not sure if they would approve of her colorful wording, I guess that‚Äôs where Erica & I differ a bit, lol. Nonetheless, I‚Äôm proud to play a Black girl who is amazing in STEM, a sarcastic history buff, boss negotiator, and athletic. Not to mention, her nails stay on point üíÖüèæ. Erica proves there‚Äôs no one way to be Black, or even smart. Smart doesn‚Äôt equate to subservient or shy. Erica gives it to you straight, delivered in a pretty relatable way ‚Äî¬† that makes her hilarious. Everyone knows an Erica. Now, you may not like her...but she‚Äôs ok with that too. I have fun playing such a rich character because she‚Äôs gonna be herself. Unapologetic, evolving, and full of surprises. I hope that Erica inspires young Black girls to stand up for what they believe in, to embrace their nerdy side and discover the beauty of their magic within!

captions:
This Transgender Awareness Week we are calling attention to our fierce, fabulous trans talent by putting them front and center with these gorgeous portraits by artist @katemoross. 

We live in a world that simultaneously erases trans excellence while benefitting from trans art, culture, and contributions, especially when it comes to trans people of color. It's especially important for cis queer people to celebrate the trans folks living and creating in our community, to uplift them and pass the mic when needed. 

Media can help raise awareness, and we as a community have a responsibility to look out for each other and provide resources to the most vulnerable among us. Let's also remember to celebrate trans folks every month, every week, and every day.
